{{!
    @template mod_scorecard/template_validation_warnings

    Block showing non-blocking validation warnings (cross-version mismatch,
    unknown fields ignored). Two display modes:
      - requireconfirmation = true : pre-import notice telling the operator
        to acknowledge via the confirmation form rendered below.
      - requireconfirmation = false: post-import informational record of what
        was ignored on import.

    Context variables required:
    * heading              - Lang string template:import:warnings:heading.
    * intro                - Lang string template:import:warnings:intro.
    * warnings             - Array of {haspath, path, message} entries.
    * requireconfirmation  - Boolean.
    * confirmtext          - Lang string template:import:warnings:confirm.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "heading": "The template imported with warnings",
        "intro": "Some fields were ignored.",
        "warnings": [],
        "requireconfirmation": true,
        "confirmtext": "Confirm below to import anyway."
    }
}}
<div class="alert alert-warning mb-3" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading">{{heading}}</h4>
    <p>{{intro}}</p>
    <ul class="mb-2">
        {{#warnings}}
        <li>{{#haspath}}<code>{{path}}</code>: {{/haspath}}{{message}}</li>
        {{/warnings}}
    </ul>
    {{#requireconfirmation}}
    <p class="mb-0 mt-2"><strong>{{confirmtext}}</strong></p>
    {{/requireconfirmation}}
</div>
